# Marketing assets are working files — generated images, logos, video footage,
# editing project files, exported deliverables. None of this belongs in git:
# they're heavy binary assets that change frequently and have no merge value.
#
# Only README.md is tracked by default, so future sessions know this tree exists
# and what convention it follows. Recover lost assets from:
#   - Drive 2TB (heavy assets, age-encrypted per backup posture)
#   - The original source (camera roll, design tool, etc.)
#
# Exception (added 2026-05-25): the website-intro/tv-loop/ deck and its V3
# design spec are CANONICAL brand artifacts (the TV background played during
# shoots, and the source-of-truth design doc) — kept in git so they survive
# disk loss and stay aligned across mirrors. Both are text + tiny PNGs
# (~40 KB total), no merge-friction or leak risk.

*
!.gitignore
!README.md

# V3 intro deck (canonical TV background, retired during production but kept as
# reference) + V3 design spec + the PNG overlay set used in DaVinci.
!website-intro/
website-intro/*
!website-intro/*.md
!website-intro/tv-loop/
!website-intro/tv-loop/**
!website-intro/overlays/
!website-intro/overlays/**

# Buyer personas (added 2026-05-27): canonical brand artifacts that inform
# all marketing, sales, content, and product decisions. Text + light .docx
# exports only — heavy media (video/audio drafts) stays out of git, goes
# to Drive 2TB per backup posture.
!buyer_personas/
!buyer_personas/**
buyer_personas/**/*.mp4
buyer_personas/**/*.m4a
buyer_personas/**/*.mov
buyer_personas/**/*.mkv
buyer_personas/**/*.wav
